description: Do not ask the human to review file lists or walk diffs after routine work
alwaysApply: true
---

# Human review

- After finishing a task, **do not** ask the user to review individual files, whole directory trees, or full diffs for sign-off unless they **explicitly** asked for a code review.
- Prefer a **short outcome summary** (what changed, what to run, risks) instead of enumerating paths.
- Do **not** paste large unchanged boilerplate or entire handover/spec documents into chat to “please confirm”.
